q- Apply a change on every element in the dataframe ? 
a- DataFrame.applymap(func, na_action=None, **kwargs) ; https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.applymap.html

q- sorting objects in a column based on labels and axis ?
a- DataFrame.sort_index(axis=0, level=None, ascending=True, inplace=False, kind='quicksort', na_position='last', sort_remaining=True, ignore_index=False, key=None); https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.sort_index.html

q- are values in the series unique ?
a- Series.is_unique ; https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.Series.is_unique.html

q- data is space seperated ?
a- pd.read_csv(your file name, delim_whitespace = True) ; https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.read_csv.html

q- few columns to be considered as dates ? 
a- pd.read_csv(your file name, parse_dates= give a list of columns you want arranged as dates) ;https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.read_csv.html

q- concatenate dataframes along an axis you want, can also add heirarchical axis on the concatenated axis when the labels are the same ?
a- pandas.concat(objs, axis=0, join='outer', ignore_index=False, keys=None, levels=None, names=None, verify_integrity=False, sort=False, copy=True) ; https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.concat.html

q- get an array of a range of integers ?
a- np.random.randint(low, high=None, size=None, dtype=int); https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/random/generated/numpy.random.randint.html

q- get the index of the maximum value along an axis ?
a- DataFrame.idxmax(axis=0, skipna=True) ; https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.idxmax.html

q- return the first 'n' rows of the largest values in required dataframe ? 
a- DataFrame.nlargest(n, columns, keep='first') ; https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.nlargest.html

q- sum of values over a required axis ? note the use of level, when dealing with multiindex axis
a- DataFrame.sum(axis=None, skipna=True, level=None, numeric_only=None, min_count=0, **kwargs) ; https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.sum.html

q- Remove duplicate rows, you can control which columns to focus for duplicates on, which occurence to keep ?
a- DataFrame.drop_duplicates(subset=None, keep='first', inplace=False, ignore_index=False);https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.drop_duplicates.html
